{
  "texts": [
    "GA application for 6-DOFIn this subsection, the representation of the problem and details about genetic operators specific to 6-DOF case study are discussed.",
    "RepresentationFor 6-DOF each chromosome is represented by a vector consisting of 6 numerical values.",
    "These values correspond to the joint angles of the robot, measured in radians, which dictate the robot's posture and movement capabilities within its operational space.",
    "The six elements of the chromosome represent the angles for each of the robot's joints, ranging from the base to the end-effector.",
    "These angles are constrained within specific limits to ensure the robot's movements are physically feasible and safe."
  ]
}